.TH SHRUTZ 1 "2025" "shrutz" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
shrutz \- active-time wallpaper rotator for macOS
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B shrutz
.I command
.RI [ args ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B shrutz
is a wallpaper rotation daemon for macOS that only counts time you are
actively using your computer. The timer ticks only when keyboard or mouse
input has been detected within the last 60 seconds. Walk away and the
timer freezes exactly where it left off.
.PP
Wallpapers are applied across every Mission Control Space simultaneously
by writing directly into the macOS wallpaper store
.RI ( Index.plist )
and restarting the wallpaper agent.
.PP
Images are organised into named
.I sets
under
.IR ~/.local/lib/shrutz/wallpapers/ .
Only one set is active at a time. Switching sets changes the wallpaper
pool immediately without resetting the active-time counter.
.SH DAEMON COMMANDS
.TP
.B shrutz status
Show whether the launchd daemon is running, its PID, and last exit code.
.TP
.B shrutz start
Load and start the launchd agent.
.TP
.B shrutz stop
Unload and stop the launchd agent.
.TP
.B shrutz log
Stream the live activity log with
.BR tail (1).
Interrupt with Ctrl-C.
.TP
.B shrutz update
Pull the latest version from the git repository recorded at install time,
re-run
.BR install.sh ,
and restart the daemon. Requires the repo to still be present on disk.
.SH PLAYBACK COMMANDS
.TP
.B shrutz now
Print the current wallpaper filename, set name, position in the set,
active-time progress, and time remaining until the next switch.
Appends
.B [PAUSED]
if the timer is frozen.
.TP
.B shrutz next
Advance immediately to the next wallpaper. The active-time counter is
not affected.
.TP
.B shrutz prev
Go back to the previous wallpaper. The active-time counter is
not affected.
.TP
.B shrutz pause
Freeze the active-time counter. The daemon keeps running and the
wallpaper stays put until
.B shrutz resume
is called.
.TP
.B shrutz resume
Unfreeze the active-time counter.
.TP
.B shrutz dash
Open a live terminal dashboard that refreshes every 5 seconds.
Displays the current wallpaper, timer progress bar, daemon uptime,
total switch count, and the last five history entries.
Press
.B q
to exit.
.SH SET COMMANDS
.TP
.B shrutz sets
List all wallpaper sets with image count, creation date, and a marker
indicating the active set.
.TP
.BI "shrutz set create " "name " [ source-path ]
Create a new wallpaper set. If
.I source-path
is provided, images from that path are imported into the new set
immediately.
.TP
.BI "shrutz set delete " name
Delete a wallpaper set and all its images after a confirmation prompt.
The active set cannot be deleted; switch to another set first.
.TP
.BI "shrutz set rename " "old new"
Rename a wallpaper set. If the renamed set is currently active,
.B ACTIVE_SET
in the state file is updated and the daemon is restarted.
.TP
.BI "shrutz set info " name
Show detailed information about a set: creation date, image count, disk
usage. For the active set, also shows current position and timer progress.
.TP
.BI "shrutz set shuffle " "name " "on" | "off"
Enable or disable shuffle mode for a set. When enabled, the daemon
generates a random play order that covers every image before repeating.
The active-time counter is not affected when shuffle is toggled.
.TP
.BI "shrutz switch " set
Switch the active wallpaper set. The wallpaper changes immediately and
position resets to the first image of the new set. The active-time
counter is preserved.
.TP
.BI "shrutz import " path " [" --set " " name ]"
Copy supported images from
.I path
(a file or directory) into the active set. Use
.B --set
.I name
to import into a specific set without switching to it. Duplicates
(matched by filename) are skipped. Supported formats:
.BR .jpg ,
.BR .jpeg ,
.BR .png ,
.BR .heic ,
.BR .webp .
.TP
.BI "shrutz export " "set " [ destination ]
Create a
.B .zip
archive of a wallpaper set including its metadata. Destination defaults
to
.IR ~/Desktop .
.SH INFO COMMANDS
.TP
.B shrutz stats
Show daemon uptime, total wallpaper switches, number of sets, total
image count, active set name, and current timer progress.
.TP
.BI "shrutz history " [ n ]
Show the last
.I n
wallpaper switches from the activity log, formatted as a table with
timestamp, position, and filename.
.I n
defaults to 10.
.TP
.B shrutz config
Print the current tunable values.
.TP
.BI "shrutz config " "key value"
Set a tunable and restart the daemon so it takes effect immediately.
Valid keys:
.RS
.TP
.B ACTIVE_MINS
Minutes of real active use before advancing to the next wallpaper.
Default: 30.
.TP
.B IDLE_THRESHOLD
Seconds without keyboard or mouse input before the user is considered
away and the timer freezes. Default: 60.
.TP
.B CHECK_EVERY
How often the daemon polls idle time and checks for mismatches, in
seconds. Default: 30.
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/bin/shrutz
The main executable.
.TP
.I ~/.local/lib/shrutz/wallpapers/<set>/
Wallpaper image directories. Each set contains a
.B __init__
metadata file (name, created date, image count, optional shuffle flag).
.TP
.I ~/.local/lib/shrutz/state
Bash-sourceable key=value file persisting runtime state across reboots:
.BR CURRENT_INDEX ,
.BR ACTIVE_SECONDS ,
.BR ACTIVE_SET ,
.BR PAUSED ,
.BR PLAY_ORDER ,
.BR SHRUTZ_REPO .
.TP
.I ~/.local/lib/shrutz/shrutz.log
Activity log. Written by the daemon on every significant event.
.TP
.I ~/.local/lib/shrutz/shrutz.err
Standard error output from the daemon. Useful for crash diagnosis.
.TP
.I ~/.local/etc/launchd/local.shrutz.plist
launchd agent definition. Source of truth; symlinked into
.IR ~/Library/LaunchAgents/ .
.TP
.I ~/Library/Application\ Support/com.apple.wallpaper/Store/Index.plist
macOS wallpaper store (binary plist). Written by shrutz on every
wallpaper switch to update all Mission Control Spaces simultaneously.
.SH SIGNALS
The daemon responds to the following signals:
.TP
.B SIGUSR1
Advance to the next wallpaper immediately (sent by
.BR "shrutz next" ).
.TP
.B SIGUSR2
Go back to the previous wallpaper (sent by
.BR "shrutz prev" ).
.TP
.B SIGHUP
Toggle pause/resume (sent by
.B shrutz pause
and
.BR "shrutz resume" ).
.TP
.B SIGTERM
Restart (sent by
.BR "shrutz switch" ,
.BR "shrutz set rename" ,
and
.BR "shrutz config" ).
launchd with
.B KeepAlive=true
restarts the daemon automatically.
.SH REQUIREMENTS
macOS 14 Sonoma or later. bash and python3 (both ship with macOS).
No third-party dependencies.
.SH INSTALLATION
.nf
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/shrutz.git
cd shrutz
chmod +x shrutz install.sh
./install.sh
.fi
.PP
After installation, reload your shell and drop images into
.IR ~/.local/lib/shrutz/wallpapers/default/ ,
or use
.B shrutz import
to bring them in.
.SH UNINSTALL
.nf
shrutz stop
rm ~/Library/LaunchAgents/local.shrutz.plist
rm -rf ~/.local/bin/shrutz \\
       ~/.local/lib/shrutz \\
       ~/.local/etc/launchd/local.shrutz.plist \\
       ~/.local/share/man/man1/shrutz.1
.fi
.PP
Also remove the
.B PATH
and
.B MANPATH
lines added by the installer from your
.I .zshrc
or
.IR .bashrc .
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR launchctl (1),
.BR launchd (8),
.BR osascript (1),
.BR ioreg (8)
